<section xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>29-305.41</num>
  <heading>Voting agreements.</heading>
  <para>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>Two or more shareholders may provide for the manner in which they will vote their shares by signing an agreement for that purpose. A voting agreement created under this section shall not be subject to § <cite path="§29-305.40">29-305.40</cite>.</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>A voting agreement created under this section shall be specifically enforceable.</text>
  </para>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 18-378" type="History">July 2, 2011, D.C. Law 18-378, § 2, 58 DCR 1720</annotation>
    <annotation type="Section References">This section is referenced in § <cite path="§29-305.22">29-305.22</cite>.</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>
